Description: The Fender Deluxe Lone Star Stratocaster is designed to rock with tone as big as Texas itself. Based on a vintage-style Strat, the Lonestar is hot-rodded with plenty of sonic and player friendly upgrades that make this one killer electric guitar for a great price. Texas Special single-coil pickups in the neck and middle position are paired with a Fender Twin Head humbucking pickup in the bridge position for the ultimate, fat sounding super Strat tone. An S-1 switch hidden discreetly in the center of the volume knob splits the bridge pickup for single-coil tone and the 5-way switch provides added versatility. Other features include a tinted Maple neck with Rosewood fingerboard, large '70s-style headstock, "modern C" profile with 9.5" radius and 22 Medium Jumbo frets. A three-ply mint green pickguard, aged white control knobs, and vintage-style synchronized tremolo bridge and also standard. The Fender Deluxe Lone Star Stratocaster electric guitar delivers a lot of bang for the buck. The solid Alder body sports a trio of great sounding pickups that are carefully chosen to cover sonic ground from soft and smooth to dirty and mean. The HSS configuration combined with the S-1 switch and 5-way give the Deluxe Lone Star Strat seven possible pickup combinations. Includes fender gig bag.
Title: Fender Deluxe Lone Star Stratocaster
